<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>SKEC - Course Overview</title>
<style>
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@600;700;800&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap');

:root {
--bg-black: #05070a;
--teal-bright: #2dd4bf;
--white: #f4faf9;
}

* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

body {
min-height: 100vh;
background:
radial-gradient(circle at 90% 10%, rgba(20,184,166,0.55) 0%, rgba(20,184,166,0.15) 30%, transparent 55%),
radial-gradient(circle at 0% 90%, rgba(88,28,135,0.35) 0%, transparent 45%),
var(--bg-black);
font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
padding: 40px 24px;
}

.container {
max-width: 800px;
margin: 0 auto;
}

.back-button {
background: rgba(20,184,166,0.1);
border: 1px solid rgba(45,212,191,0.5);
color: var(--teal-bright);
padding: 10px 20px;
border-radius: 8px;
cursor: pointer;
font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
margin-bottom: 40px;
transition: background 0.2s ease;
}

.back-button:hover {
background: rgba(20,184,166,0.2);
}

h1 {
font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
font-weight: 800;
font-size: 48px;
color: var(--teal-bright);
margin-bottom: 40px;
}

.modules {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: 1fr;
gap: 20px;
}

.module-card {
background: rgba(20,184,166,0.06);
border: 1.5px solid rgba(45,212,191,0.5);
border-radius: 12px;
padding: 24px;
cursor: pointer;
transition: transform 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
}

.module-card:hover {
transform: translateY(-2px);
background: rgba(20,184,166,0.12);
border-color: var(--teal-bright);
}

.module-card h2 {
font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
font-weight: 700;
font-size: 18px;
color: var(--white);
margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.module-card p {
font-size: 14px;
color: rgba(244,250,249,0.7);
line-height: 1.4;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
<button class="back-button" onclick="window.location.href='index.html'">← Back to Start</button>

<h1>All Modules</h1>

<div class="modules">
<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 1: Teacher Standards & Reflection')">
<h2>1. Teacher Standards &amp; Reflection</h2>
<p>Explore teacher standards, celebrate your choice to teach English, and understand the value of continuous professional development.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 2: Narrative Writing')">
<h2>2. Narrative Writing</h2>
<p>Learn what stories look like with minimal prep, operationalize creative writing, and master write-along examples and tasks.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 3: Persuasive Writing')">
<h2>3. Persuasive Writing</h2>
<p>Compare weaker and stronger models, teach correlation versus causality, and help pupils build powerful arguments.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 4: Analytical Writing')">
<h2>4. Analytical Writing</h2>
<p>Examine grade boundaries, scaffold skills with sentence-by-sentence models, and explore analytical frameworks and bookmarks.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 5: Literature &amp; Unseen Poetry')">
<h2>5. Literature &amp; Unseen Poetry</h2>
<p>Teach themes and comparison as skills, use visual scaffolds like boxes, and apply PAINFUL and POETIC frameworks.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 6: Macbeth')">
<h2>6. Macbeth</h2>
<p>Explore characters, plot, themes, and writer's intentions. Learn to grade and moderate essays effectively.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 7: Romeo &amp; Juliet')">
<h2>7. Romeo &amp; Juliet</h2>
<p>Dive into Shakespeare's tragedy with the same depth as Macbeth, covering characters, themes, and essay techniques.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 8: A Christmas Carol &amp; Jekyll &amp; Hyde')">
<h2>8. A Christmas Carol &amp; Jekyll &amp; Hyde</h2>
<p>Study Victorian literature with focus on characters, themes, social context, and essay craft.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 9: An Inspector Calls &amp; Animal Farm')">
<h2>9. An Inspector Calls &amp; Animal Farm</h2>
<p>Examine modern and allegorical drama, exploring power, responsibility, and social messaging.</p>
</div>

<div class="module-card" onclick="alert('Module 10: How to Improve Student Work')">
<h2>10. How to Improve Student Work</h2>
<p>Learn practical strategies for giving feedback, using sentence-by-sentence activities, and moving work from good to great.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
